oc:kn_236fe379 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Full test campaign execution" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Create subagent test harness. 2. Run NULL baseline on all 4 scenarios. 3. Test each variant on same scenarios. 4. Compare compliance rates. 5. Identify which rationalizations break through. 6. Iterate on winning variant to close holes." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Systematic iteration identifies the strongest documentation variant while closing discovered loopholes" ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

oc:kn_35ead3ba a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing test scenarios for skill compliance" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Best pressure scenarios combine 3+ pressures simultaneously: time pressure + sunk cost + authority + exhaustion. Single-pressure scenarios are too easy for agents to resist." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Agents rationalize away single pressures but combined pressures reveal true compliance strength of documentation" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_5b143754 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Setting expectations for test results" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Expected compliance by variant: NULL (no awareness), Variant A soft suggestion (skips under pressure), Variant B directive (sometimes checks, easy to rationalize away), Variant C emphatic (strong but rigid), Variant D process-oriented (balanced but longer)" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Knowing expected outcomes helps identify unexpected test results that reveal new compliance failure modes" .

oc:kn_711201bd a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Testing any CLAUDE.md documentation variant" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Run NULL baseline (no skills doc) — record agent choices and rationalizations verbatim. 2. Run variant with same scenario — check if agent discovers/uses skills. 3. Pressure test — add time/sunk cost/authority pressures, document when compliance breaks. 4. Meta-test — ask agent why they didn't comply, how doc could improve." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Structured comparison ensures each variant is evaluated against the same baseline, producing comparable compliance data" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_778f9d8a a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Evaluating test results" ;
    oc:directiveContent "A variant succeeds only if: agent checks for skills unprompted, reads skill completely before acting, follows guidance under pressure, and cannot rationalize away compliance" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Partial compliance (e.g., checking but not reading fully) indicates documentation that agents will bypass in production" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_7816fa0b a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating pressure scenarios" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Four pressure dimensions to test: Time Pressure + Confidence (emergency stakes), Sunk Cost + Works Already (invested effort), Authority + Speed Bias (partner wants speed), Familiarity + Efficiency (I already know how)" ;
    oc:hasRationale "These four dimensions cover the most common real-world pressures that cause agents to skip skill usage" .

oc:kn_a44fe467 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When choosing documentation style for CLAUDE.md" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Soft suggestion documentation ('Consider checking skills') fails under pressure — agents skip it. Directive documentation without explicit process steps also fails. Emphatic ALL-CAPS may feel rigid but produces stronger compliance." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Testing showed graduated compliance: NULL < Soft Suggestion < Directive < Emphatic < Process-Oriented, with pressure being the differentiator" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b9bd6bf8 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing test scenarios" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Good pressure scenarios use concrete A/B/C options (not open-ended), real file paths, specific consequences, and force agent to act ('What do you do?' not 'What should you do?')" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Concrete forced-choice scenarios prevent agents from giving academic answers and reveal actual behavior under pressure" .

oc:req_080388d4 a oc:RequirementKnowledge ;
    oc:isOptional false ;
    oc:requirementValue "Understanding of TDD RED-GREEN-REFACTOR cycle (superpowers:test-driven-development)" .

